-- Mercedes-Benz car sales in US drop 3 percent in Dec
-- 
-- Thu Jan 3, 2008 2:04pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/03/us-mercedes-carsales-idUSL0317181020080103

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - Daimler AG's ( DAIGn.DE ) premium Mercedes-Benz Cars division said on Thursday it sold 3 percent fewer cars in the United States in December than a year ago. 

 The company sold 27,301 vehicles last month, compared with 28,115 cars in the same month a year earlier, it said. Total car sales in 2007 still increased 2.2 percent to 253,433 units, it said. (Reporting by  Peter Dinkloh )